ðŸ“Œ TABLE 2: Algorithms & Concepts (What You Learn)

Purpose: Show ML, DL, and data depth

| Phase   | Algorithms / Concepts                                                           |
| ------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Phase 1 | Lag features, rolling statistics, normalization, outlier handling               |
| Phase 2 | Partitioning, window functions, aggregations                                    |
| Phase 3 | Schema enforcement, deduplication, data quality checks                          |
| Phase 4 | Linear, Logistic, Ridge, Lasso, Decision Tree, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting |
| Phase 5 | Cross-validation, ROC-AUC, precision/recall, feature importance                 |
| Phase 6 | LSTM, GRU, dropout, early stopping, sliding windows                             |
| Phase 7 | Volatility modeling, regime detection, probability calibration                  |
| Phase 8 | Experiment tracking, model versioning, reproducibility                          |
| Phase 9 | Confidence thresholds, ensemble logic, trade filtering                          |

